      "concepts": [
        "Information Theory and Shannon Entropy"
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Chaining Probabilities: Markov Chains and N-gram Models",
      "scope": "Armed with a way to measure predictability, we examine the earliest algorithmic attempts at text generation using Markov Chains. We will explore how 'n-gram' models assume that the next word depends only on a short, fixed history of previous words, providing our first real generative engine.",
