      "title": "Decoding the Message: The 'Noisy Channel' Model",
      "scope": "Finally, we explore how these early generative concepts were applied to complex sequence tasks like machine translation. By framing translation as deciphering a message corrupted by a 'noisy channel' (e.g., treating French as 'noisy' English), we set the conceptual stage for the sequence-to-sequence translation problems the Transformer was explicitly built to conquer.",
      "concepts": [
        "The 'Noisy Channel' model of translation"
